    <section>
     <title>Bitmap Format constants</title>
     <table>
      <tgroup cols='2'>
       <thead>
        <row>
         <entry>name</entry>
         <entry>descrpition</entry>
        </row>
       </thead>
      <tbody>

        <row>
         <entry>
          <constant id='constantcairo-format-argb32'>CAIRO_FORMAT_ARGB32</constant>
          (<link linkend='language.types.integer'>integer</link>)
         </entry>
         <entry>     Each pixel is a 32-bit quantity, with alpha in the upper 8 bits, 
     then red, then green, then blue. The 32-bit quantities are stored 
     native-endian. Pre-multiplied alpha is used. (That is, 50% 
     transparent red is 0x80800000, not 0x80ff0000.)
</entry>
        </row>


        <row>
         <entry>
          <constant id='constantcairo-format-rgb24'>CAIRO_FORMAT_RGB24</constant>
          (<link linkend='language.types.integer'>integer</link>)
         </entry>
         <entry>     Each pixel is a 32-bit quantity, with the upper 8 bits unused. 
     Red, Green, and Blue are stored in the remaining 24 bits in that order.
</entry>
        </row>


        <row>
         <entry>
          <constant id='constantcairo-format-a8'>CAIRO_FORMAT_A8</constant>
          (<link linkend='language.types.integer'>integer</link>)
         </entry>
         <entry>     Each pixel is a 8-bit quantity holding an alpha value.
</entry>
        </row>


        <row>
         <entry>
          <constant id='constantcairo-format-a1'>CAIRO_FORMAT_A1</constant>
          (<link linkend='language.types.integer'>integer</link>)
         </entry>
         <entry>     Each pixel is a 1-bit quantity holding an alpha value. Pixels are packed 
     together into 32-bit quantities. The ordering of the bits matches the 
     endianess of the platform. On a big-endian machine, the first pixel is 
     in the uppermost bit, on a little-endian machine the first pixel is in 
     the least-significant bit.
</entry>
        </row>


        <row>
         <entry>
          <constant id='constantcairo-format-rgb16-565'>CAIRO_FORMAT_RGB16_565</constant>
          (<link linkend='language.types.integer'>integer</link>)
         </entry>
         <entry>     Each pixel is a 16-bit quantity, with red in the upper 5 bits, 
     then green in the next 6, then blue in the lowest 5 bits.
</entry>
        </row>

     </tbody>
    </tgroup>
   </table>
